  "description": [
    "Page 8 MIDLAND COOPERATOR Published SemiMonthly for MIDLAND COOPERATIVE WHOLESALE By Cooperative Press Inc 63rd Penn Ave S Minneapolis Minn EDITORIAL OFFICE 739 Johnson St NE Minneapolis Subscription price 25 cents per year Entered as second class matter at the post office at Minne apolis Minn under the act of March 3 1879 EditorJoseph Gilbert Associate Editorslver Lind and Davis Douthit Cooperative Expansion One of the principles of the Consumers Cooperative movement is Expansion This is what makes it a move ment instead of being merely another way of doing busi ness There are many in the cooperative movement who are unconscious of the necessity for expansion and espe cially is this so with socalled independent cooperatives There are a great many oil cooperatives in this country especially in this middle northwestern tenitoiy which are quite selfsatisfied in just conducting an iso lated cooperative confined to dealing in petroleum prod ucts and a few auto accessories Many of these associa tions are what might be considered successful judged by the fact that they are able to meet competition and distribute patronage refunds to their members and pa trons But what is to be the future of such cooperatives The answer"
  ],
